            <title>[FELIX-3534] ServiceFactory components don&apos;t deal with ConfigurationAdmin updates properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3534</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ImmediateComponentManager.modify doesn&apos;t deal with ServiceFactory components since it decides whether to try to update existing components by seeing if getInstance()  returns null.  A ServiceFactory component can have any number of instances and all should be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
